<h2>Sunday, October 26 / Domingo 26 de Octubre</h2>

<p>We went to breakfast with Roberto, Flor, and Santiago to a town about a 30-min drive from Colima, toward the volcanoes: Suchitlan. This is a town that looks the same today as it probably did 80 years ago. We go there every time we visit Colima, because the food is good and you seat beneath coffee trees. For lunch, Hector’s mom cooked a traditional meal that Hector requested: "Queso Relleno" (stuffed cheese.) After a much-needed nap, we walked all afternoon in downtown. That evening we played dominoes with Karla’s mom.</p>

<p>Fuimos a desayunar a Suchitlán (una tradición cada que vamos a Colima) con Roberto, Flor, y Santiago. De regreso llegamos a ver artesanías a Comala. Comimos en casa de los papás de Héctor: Silvia cocinó un queso relleno a petición de Héctor. Después de una siesta, nos fuimos a caminar por el centro. Esa noche jugamos dominó con la mama de Karla.</p>

