<h2>Thursday, October 30 / Jueves 30 de Octubre</h2>

<p>For breakfast we went to Cronos to have crepes and then walked around the park near where Hector grew up. In the afternoon we ate at Karla’s mom’s place, and stayed there until around 6 pm, saying goodbyes to all. We stopped briefly in a park in downtown to see a cool exhibit of both, modern and prehispanic, Day of the Dead altars made out of grains, petals, pottery, and other traditional objects. We ate dinner at Hector’s parents’ place and went to bed early.</p>

<p>Nos fuimos a desayunar con Silvia a Cronos y luego caminamos por el Jardín de los Borrachos. Comimos sopitos en casa de la mamá de Karla y ahí nos quedamos hasta las 6, despidiéndonos de todos ahí. Paramos de rapidito en el Jardín Núñez a ver una exhibición de altares de muertos y nos fuimos a casa de los papás de Héctor donde cenamos y nos fuimos a acostar temprano.</p>

