INSERT INTO blogs VALUES(12,'2014-puerto-rico','Puerto Rico','2014-11-18 02:11:26.121024','2014-11-18 02:11:26.121024','<p>In May we took a much needed vacation and went to San Juan, Puerto Rico. / <span class="spanish">A mediados de mayo nos tomamos unas muy merecidas vacaciones a San Juan, Puerto Rico.</span></p>

<h2>May 15th, 2014</h2>
<p>After a scare in which our flight from State College to Philladelphia almost got cancelled, we made it to Puerto Rico without a hitch. We were starving so immediately after checking-in we walked to a little restaurant a couple of blocks from the hotel and ordered a few dishes, including the traditional <i>mofongo</i>. We then walked to the beach which is half a block from our hotel. / <span class="spanish">Despues del susto que nos llevamos cuando por poco y cancelan nuestro vuelo de State College a Filadelfia terminamos llegando a Puerto Rico sin mas contratiempos. Despues de registranos en el hotel nos fuimos a comer y luego a checar la playa que nos quedaba a media cuadra del hotel. </span></p>

<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico01_thumb.jpg" />

<p>At night we went to a little restaurant (Bebos) a few blocks from our hotel and tried Asopao (one of Puerto Rico''s stapple dishes) and a seafood salad. / <span class="spanish">En la noche fuimos a un restaurantito cerca del hotel y probamos uno de los platillos tradicionales de Puerto Rico llamado <i>asopao</i> (y conste que te corrijen si lo pronuncias como <i>asopado</i>.)</span></p>

<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico02_thumb.jpg" />

<p>We called it a night early and went back to our hotel. / <span class="spanish">Despues de la cena nos fuimos tempranito a dormir.</span></p>

<h2>May 16th</h2>
<h3>Viejo San Juan</h3>
<p>On Friday we woke up early and had breakfast in a hip cafe (Kamoli) close to our hotel. From there we took the bus (guagua) to Viejo San Juan, the old part of the city. We walked around the narrow streets surrounded by beautiful colonial buildings and colorful houses. It was incredibly sunny and we went on a mission to find a hat for Karla. Turns out she''s got a small head and it was hard to find a hat that fit her, but we eventually did. / <span class="spanish">El viernes nos despertamos tempranito y desayunamos en un cafe muy bonito cerca del hotel. De ahi tomamos el camion (la guagua) y nos fuimos al Viejo San Juan, la parte colonial de la ciudad que tiene una arquitectura preciosa y unas casas muy pintorescas. Como el dia estaba muy soleado decidimos comprarle un sombrero a Karla pero resulto que tiene la cabeza muy chica y casi ninguno le quedaba. Finalmente encontramos uno muy bonito que le quedo justo a la medida.</span></p>
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico03_thumb.jpg" />
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico04_thumb.jpg" />
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico05_thumb.jpg" />
