<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico29_thumb.jpg" />

<h4>Flan de Coco</h4>
<p>After walking for several hours at El Morro we went for dinner to a Spanish restaurant. Although the meal was amazing, the highlight of the dinner was the dessert, a superb <i>flan de coco</i>. There are no pictures of the dessert, but the pictures below are proof that we enjoyed it. / <span class="spanish">Despues de caminar varias horas en el Morro terminamos en un restaurante español y nos echamos unas tapas incluyendo unos callos a la madrileña. La comida estuvo de primera, pero el postre (un flan de coco) fue el que se robo la tarde como se puede apreciar en las fotos.</span></p>
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico30_thumb.jpg" />
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico31_thumb.jpg" />
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico32_thumb.jpg" />

<p>After dinner we walked around the town a bit more. / <span class="spanish">Despues de cenar caminamos un poquito mas por el Viejo San Juan.</span></p>
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico33_thumb.jpg" />
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico34_thumb.jpg" />
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico35_thumb.jpg" />

<h3>May 17th</h3>
<h4>Sunrise</h4>
<p>On Saturday Hector woke up early and went to see the sunrise and walk around the beach for a while. / <span class="spanish">El sabado Hector se desperto tempranito para alcanzar a ver el amanecer y caminar por la playa.</span></p>
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico36_thumb.jpg" />
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico37_thumb.jpg" />
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico38_thumb.jpg" />

<h4>At the beach</h4>
<p>In the afternoon we went back to the beach for a swim. / <span class="spanish">En la tarde regresamos a la playa para darnos un chapuzon.</span></p>
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico39_thumb.jpg" />
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico40_thumb.jpg" />

<h4>Fancy Dinner</h4>
<p>We found a recommended fancy restaurant (Santaella) not far from our hotel and we decided to try it tonight. On our way to the restaurant we stopped by a small plaza to drink a couple of beers while listening to live music and watch people dance. After dinner we took a cab back to our hotel. Little did we know that the driver was going to drive (on purpose) a whole block the wrong way to avoid getting caught in the Saturday night traffic. Boy that was an adventure! / <span class="spanish">En una de las guias vimos recomendado un restaurante medio elegante que nos quedaba relativamente cerca del hotel y decidimos cenar ahi. En camino al restaurante pasamos por una plaza en la que habia musica viva y gente bailando, muy puerto riqueña la cosa. Despues de la cena tomamos un taxi de regreso al hotel y la sorpresota que nos dimos cuando el taxista decidio manejar en sentido contrario por una calle para evitar el trafico de la noche! </span></p>

<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico41_thumb.jpg" />

<h3>May 18th</h3>
<h4>Sunrise (again!)</h4>
<p>Today I convinced Karla to wake up really early and come to watch the sunrise with me. / <span class="spanish">Hoy convenci a Karla que se levante temprano y me acompañe a ver el amanecer en la playa. </span></p>
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico42_thumb.jpg" />
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico43_thumb.jpg" />
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico44_thumb.jpg" />
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico45_thumb.jpg" />
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico46_thumb.jpg" />
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico47_thumb.jpg" />

<h4>Viejo San Juan (part II)</h4>
<p>After watching the sunrise we went back to sleep for several hours before heading out to Viejo San Juan again. / <span class="spanish">Despues de disfrutar la salida del sol nos regresamos al cuarto y nos volvimos a dormir por varias horas antes de levantarnos de nuevo y salir a pasear. </span></p>
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico48_thumb.jpg" />
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico49_thumb.jpg" />
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico50_thumb.jpg" />

<h4>Castillo de San Cristobal</h4>
<p>Today we visited the second castle in this part of town: El Castillo de San Cristobal. This one is as amazing as El Morro and so are the views. / <span class="spanish">Hoy visitamos el segundo castillo en el Viejo San Juan, el Castillo de San Cristobal, que al igual que el Morro es impresionante y con unas vistas preciosas del mar y de la ciudad. </span></p>
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico51_thumb.jpg" />
