<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico61_thumb.jpg" />

<h4>Rum and more rum</h4>
<p>After visiting El Castillo de San Cristobal we stopped at a bar and finally tried Puerto Rican rum. Karla had a mjoito and Hector had a rum on the rocks. We also tried an appetizer called <i>alcapurrias</i> which are fried yuca and plantain dough filled with pork. They were gooooood. I am sure the rum helped too :) / <span class="spanish">Despues del Castillo de San Cristobal nos paramos en bar a tomar finalmente un ron puerto riqueño. Hector se tomo un ron con hielo y Karla pidio un mojito. Tambien probamos un platillo que se llama <i>alcapurrias</i> que es una cruza entre un tamal y una flauta, pero la harina es de yuca y de platano macho. Muy rico. </span></p>
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico62_thumb.jpg" />
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico63_thumb.jpg" />
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico64_thumb.jpg" />
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico65_thumb.jpg" />

<p>After this bar we went to another one that had outdoor sitting. We drank a couple of beers while we listened to an old man play the accordion and share his views of life and the universe with us. Lovely way to enjoy the town. / <span class="spanish">Despues de este bar nos fuimos a otro que tenia sillas en las afueras y nos toco oir a un viejito tocar el acordeon y compartir con nostros su filosofia de la vida y el universo, definitivamente una manera muy bonita de pasar la tarde en las calles del Viejo San Juan. </span></p>
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico96_thumb.jpg" />

<p>On our way back to the hotel we stopped at Bebos for dinner and we tried another Puerto Rican stapple called <i>fricasse</i>. We had one with rabbit and other with goat. Yummy. / <span class="spanish">De regreso al hotel regresamos al restaurante Bebos y de cena probamos otro platillo tradicional de Puerto Rico que se llama <i>fricasse</i>, pedimos uno de conejo y otro de cabrito...para chuparse los dedos! </span></p>
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico95_thumb.jpg" />

<h3>May 19th</h3>
<h4>At the beach and the pool</h4>
<p>Today we went back to the beach but since the winds were a bit strong and the waves larger than in previous days we also went to the pool that was in front of our hotel room. Life is hard! / <span class="spanish">Hoy fuimos a la playa, pero como el mar estaba un poco picado solo Hector se metio a nadar asi que de regreso llegamos a la alberca del hotel que esta justo enfrente de nuestro cuarto. </span></p>
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico66_thumb.jpg" />
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico67_thumb.jpg" />
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico68_thumb.jpg" />

<h4>Dinner</h4>
<p>For dinner we walked to another small hotel near to us that had a little restaurant next to the beach. / <span class="spanish">Para cenar nos fuimos un restaurante cerca de nuestro hotel, a la orilla de la playa. </span></p>
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico69_thumb.jpg" />
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico70_thumb.jpg" />
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico71_thumb.jpg" />

<h3>May 20th</h3>
<h4>Breakfast at Kamoli''s</h4>
<p>Today is our last full day in town. We started with a breakfast a Kamoli''s before heading back to the old town one last time. / <span class="spanish">Hoy es nuestro ultimo dia de paseo en San Juan. Para desayunar regresamos a Kamoli''s, el cafe cerca de nuestro hotel y de ahi nos fuimos una vez mas al Viejo San Juan para comprar algunas artesanias y chucherias.</span></p>
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico72_thumb.jpg" />
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico73_thumb.jpg" />

<h4>Viejo San Juan (part III)</h4>
<p>We arrived to Viejo San Juan rather early and we had the streets to ourselves. We walked through several streets that we missed the first couple of times and stopped in some of the art galleries along the way. / <span class="spanish">Llegamos muy temprano al Viejo San Juan asi que nos toco ver las calles sin carros ni trafico, muy bonitas. </span></p>
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico74_thumb.jpg" />
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2014/puertorico75_thumb.jpg" />
