INSERT INTO blogs VALUES(19,'2013-maine','Maine','2014-11-18 02:11:26.293816','2014-12-01 04:19:10.889380','<h2>July 10 - Leaving Home / Saliendo de casa</h2>
<p>We left home, crossed parts of Pennsylvania, New Jersey, and New York, and arrived in Mystic, Connecticut in time to see the weight bridge rise up to let a tall sailing boat through. We walked around town and ate at S&amp;P Oyster, Co. a tasty meal that included gazpacho, scallops, corn tamale, haddock in cacique sauce, and good beer. /&nbsp;<span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102);">Salimos de casa, y cruzamos parte de los estados de Pensilvania, Nueva Jersey y Nueva York, y llegamos al pueblo de Mystic en Conecticut donde pasamos la noche. En el pueblo hay un puente de pesas que nos toco ver en acci&oacute;n cuando lo levantaron para que pasara un velero. Cenamos rico en un restaurante al aire libre.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine002_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine003_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine004_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<h2>July 11 - Arriving to Maine / Llegando a Maine</h2>
<p>We drove through parts of Rhode Island, Massachusetts, and New Hampshire. And as soon as we entered Maine we took exit #3 to check out the shopping experience. &nbsp;We looked at tents and other camping, kayaking, and sports equipment at the Kittery Trading Post and after seeing a couple more stores, we drove near the coast, getting glimpses of the water. As it was getting late and we were still some distance from our inn, we went back into the highway and exited in Brunswick, where we headed for the Harpswells. &nbsp;We passed some rural and working areas before we reached our inn, almost by the water, overseeing the bay. We checked in and went for dinner to The Dolphin, a place recommended by Anne, our innkeeper. &nbsp;The place was surrounded by fog! The meal was great but the best parts were the blueberry muffins that came with each plate and the tip from our server to a local lobster shack. / <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102);">Despues de dejar Conecticut y pasar partes de los estados de Rhode Island, Masachusets y Nueva Hampshire, llegamos al estado de Maine. Tomamos una salida de la carretera para bobear en unas tiendas en el pueblo de Kittery. Luego manejamos por la costa y despu&eacute;s seguimos rumbo al pueblo de Harspwells, donde pasaremos las siguientes 4 noches. Esa noche cenamos en el restaurante El Delf&iacute;n, por recomendaci&oacute;n de la due&ntilde;a de la posada.</span></p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine005_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine006_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<h2>July 12 - The Harpswells</h2>
<p>After a fail attempt at jogging by the road with a non-existing shoulder and then moving up and down the side road, avoiding a dog, we barely made it to breakfast at the inn. After that we drove to Orr and Bailey islands, all connected with bridges. At the tip of Baileys is Land&rsquo;s End and we stopped there for a bit. We then drove around the same area to the Giant Stairs and walked by the bluffs and rocks. For lunch we went to the local lobster shack recommended to us: Morse&rsquo;s, right by the bridge between Orr and Bailey islands. We enjoyed a two-lobster, steamers, and corn platter. &nbsp;We even saw the fishing ship stop by their pier to drop a fresh catch, duly headed to the steaming pots to then reach our plates. After lunch, we drove through the Great Island to Cundy&rsquo;s Point and saw more working ships and shops. &nbsp;We stopped at a General Store for some wine, cheese, and fruit and went back to the inn for a nap (Karla&rsquo;s allergies make her sleepy). &nbsp;We borrowed some utensils from the innkeepers and headed to the Adirondack chairs on the lawn by the water and had our dinner there. A couple from Pittsburgh joined us and we lit a fire and chatted until late. / <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102);">En la ma&ntilde;ana tratamos de ir a correr pero no hab&iacute;a mucho acotamiento en la carretera. Despu&eacute;s de desayunar nos fuimos a turistear por las muchas islas en la zona, conectadas por puentes y carreteras. Fuimos a un lugar llamado Land&rsquo;s End (Fin de la Tierra) y a una playa rocosa con la Escalinata Gigante, con bufadora y toda la cosa. Para lonchar fuimos a una palapa de langostas, Morse&rsquo;s, donde comimos langostas con almejas. Desde nuestra mesa vimos al barco pescadero dejar su carga fresquecita. La tarde la pasamos turisteando manejando por la zona, dormimos siesta, y en la noche hicimos nuestra cena con quesos, frutas, pan y vino que compramos esa tarde en una tiendita. Cenamos en el patio con vista al oce&aacute;no y luego prendimos una fogata y nos quedamos platicando con otra pareja que se nos uni&oacute;.</span></p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine008_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine007_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine009_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine010_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine011_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine012_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine013_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine014_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine015_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine016_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine017_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine018_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine019_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine020_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine021_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine022_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine023_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine024_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine025_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine026_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine027_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine028_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine029_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<h2>July 13 - Shopping at Freeport / De compras en Freeport</h2>
<p>After breakfast we drove to Freeport to spend a glorious day shopping. Freeport houses the L.L. Bean campus, with their flagship, outlet, ski, camping, and bike stores among others. But the whole town is a mall and we spent hours browsing and shopping for clothes. &nbsp;We even indulged in some ice cream today. &nbsp;After a day of hard work, we headed back to Morse&rsquo;s since we loved it so much. We repeated the glorious dinner and drove around after that, enjoying the gorgeous sunset. /&nbsp;<span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102);">Luego de desayunar nos fuimos a la ciudad de Freeport, donde est&aacute; la tienda original de L.L. Bean. Adem&aacute;s de varias tiendas especializadas de la compa&ntilde;&iacute;a, hay otras tiendas de marca en descontinuados, as&iacute; que nos dedicamos a pasar el dia de compras. Esa noche cenamos de nuevo en la palapa de Morse&rsquo;s unas langostitas. Despu&eacute;s de cenar disfrutamos del atardecer bell&iacute;simo y manejamos por las islas.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine030_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine031_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine032_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine033_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine034_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine035_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine036_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine037_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine038_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine001_thumb.jpg" /><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine039_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine040_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine041_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine042_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;</p>
<h2>July 14 - Portland</h2>
<p>We were determined to go jogging, so this time we drove to Brunswick and jogged around Bowdoin campus; it was a hot day and we were tired from the shopping last day, but were still able to do some work. After that, we had breakfast at the Wild Oats Caf&eacute; right in town. &nbsp;Later, we drove all the way back to the Kittery Trading Post and got us a new tent (since we did not see one we liked at LL Bean). On the way there we got lost getting to Los Cocos Locos where we had lunch. [During lunch we learned that Summer had eaten a curtain!] While at the Kittery we did some more shopping and then drove on Route 1 back home, trying to see the beaches, but the traffic was horrible and there was no parking anywhere. We stopped in Portland, walked around the promenade and park. We then headed to downtown, went to the marina, saw a piece of the Berlin Wall, and bumped into a garden caf&eacute; where we had dinner. &nbsp;Before leaving Portland, we headed back to the promenade, watched the harbor and the dogs running on the big lawn. &nbsp;/&nbsp;<span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102);">Hoy manejamos al centro del pueblo cercano, donde nos estacionamos y fuimos a correr en el campus de la universidad. &nbsp;Luego desayunamos en un caf&eacute; cercano y regresamos a nuestro cuarto a cambiarnos. Fuimos a las tiendas de Kittery donde compramos una tienda de acampar. De ah&iacute; nos fuimos a la ciudad capital del estado, Portland, donde caminamos por la bahia y el centro, y cenamos en un retaurante en un jardin. Desde un parque nos toc&oacute; ver el puerto y mucha gente hacienda ejercicio o caminando a sus perros.</span></p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine043_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine044_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine045_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine046_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine047_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine048_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;</p>
<h2>July 15 - Getting to Cutler and the Little River Lighthouse / En Camino al Faro</h2>
<p>We left the inn after breakfast, stopped at the General Store for some groceries and drove towards Cutler. We stopped for lunch at 44 Degrees in Macchias and after getting lost a bit, we arrived to Cutler Harbor. We parked by the church, grabbed our sleeping bags and backpacks and waited at the ramp at the pier for our ride, looking at &ldquo;our island&rdquo;. Chuck arrived in a small boat and after we picked up Marilyn at the boat house side of the island, we drove around the whole island, seeing the lighthouse for the first time. We also got a glimpse of an eaglet attempting to fly on its nest. &nbsp;We got back to the boat house and walked the few minutes that it takes to cross the island to the sea side, where the lighthouse and the two-story house are located. The island is tiny and filed with pine trees, and the edges of the island are rugged rocks. We climbed the spiral staircase to the tip of the lighthouse and took the view in. We can see Grand Manan Island (Canada) right across from us! We took tons of photos and then sat on the chairs by the edge, seeing the tide go down and rocks appearing where there was only water before. We were told the tide changes every 6 hours and it is about 14 feet difference between low and high tides. For dinner we made grilled salmon with broccoli and bread with wine; we ate with Marilyn and Chuck &hellip; We are the only four people on this island, and our phones died by roaming and we did not bring the charger. It was great! /&nbsp;<span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102);">Salimos de las islas despu&eacute;s de desayunar ; compramos comida en una tiendita; y paramos en un restaurante para lonchar, y finalmente, despu&eacute;s de darnos una perdida, llegamos al Puerto de Cutler. Estacionamos el carro, agarramos nuestros tiliches, y nos fuimos al muelle a esperar a nuestro contacto, Chuck. &nbsp;Chuck lleg&oacute; en una lancha y nos llev&oacute; a la isla donde pasaremos las siguientes 24 horas. Una vez que su esposa Marilyn se nos uni&oacute;, le dimos la vuelta a la isla, y nos toc&oacute; ver el faro por primera vez, desde el agua. Una vez que desembarcamos y caminos los 5-10 minutos que lleva cruzar la isla, llegamos a la parte del oce&aacute;no, donde est&aacute; la casa y el faro. Nos subimos a la punta del faro, luego nos sentamos en las sillas junto al agua, y tomamos fotos de todo. Desde aqu&iacute; se ven las Islas Grand Manan, de Canad&aacute;. &nbsp;Cada seis horas sube y baja la marea, con como 4 metros y medio de diferencia entre marea alta y baja, as&iacute; que nos toc&oacute; ver aparecer rocas que estuvieron cubiertas por el agua. A nuestros celulares se les acab&oacute; la bater&iacute;a, as&iacute; que estamos completamente solos los cuatro en esta isla. &iexcl;Fant&aacute;stico!</span></p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine049_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine050_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine051_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine052_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine053_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine054_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine055_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine056_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine057_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine058_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine059_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine060_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine061_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine062_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine063_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine064_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine065_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine066_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine067_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine068_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine069_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine070_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<h2>July 16 - Enjoying &ldquo;Our&rdquo; Island /&nbsp;Disfrutando de &ldquo;nuestra&rdquo; isla</h2>
<p>We woke up at 5 am to see the sunrise and it was truly beautiful! We drank coffee by the water, seeing fishing boats and crews come and check the many lobster traps that are everywhere. We even obliged with the hand waving requested by the touristic boat that came by on their way to see the puffins. &nbsp;Karla took a nap while Hector explored the island. We had lunch by the water and left the island shortly after that. Chuck and Marilyn took us back to land and once in our car, we drove north, close to the border with Canada, to Quody Head State Park, where we saw a candy-stripped lighthouse. We stopped in a pottery shop nearby and drove towards Acadia National Park. After around 3 hours we arrived to Bar Harbor and then entered Acadia NP and got lost with detours and bad signaling. We passed many cyclists and took in the views of mountains and valleys. &nbsp;We finally found the campgrounds and pitched our new tent, started a fire, and had a fat and juicy steak with veggies for dinner. /&nbsp;<span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102);">Nos despertamos a las 5 de la ma&ntilde;ana a ver salir el sol y fue hermoso! Tomamos caf&eacute; en las sillas junto al agua y vimos llegar algunos pescadores que checaron sus trampas de langostas. Tambi&eacute;n vimos pasar un barco tur&iacute;stico, al cual saludamos como si fu&eacute;ramos los due&ntilde;os del lugar. Mientras Karla dorm&iacute;a siesta, H&eacute;ctor se fue a explorer la isla. Chuck y Marilyn nos llevaron de regreso al pueblo despu&eacute;s de lonchar. Ya en el carro, nos fuimos al norte, cerca de la frontera con Canad&aacute;, a ver otro faro, el Quody Head. De ah&iacute; regresamos al sur, camino al parque nacional Acadia y nos perdimos una vez en el parque inmenso, tratando de hallar nuestro campamento. El parque incluye varias monta&ntilde;as y playas (de hecho es una isla, comunicada por carretera con tierra). Una vez en nuestro campamento, paramos la tienda nueva, prendimos una fogata y cenamos.</span>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine071_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine072_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine073_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine074_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine075_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine076_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine077_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<p>West Quoddy</p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine078_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine079_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<h2>July 17 - Acadia National Park / Parque Nacional Acadia</h2>
<p>After breakfast we drove to Seal Harbor where Hector decided to go for a swim. Since the water was in the mid-60s, Karla decided to read by the beach instead. &nbsp;We then drove to Bar Harbor and went into some of the town shops, and then tried our first lobster roll with a blueberry beer (apparently Maine is a blueberry producer). We then drove to Cadillac Mountain where we walked to the top and enjoyed the views. On the way down we stopped at Jordan Pond and walked around a little. Back to camp, we made dinner and went to bed early, and woke up in the middle of the night to a thunderstorm (yes, our tent was surrounded by pine trees). &nbsp;The tent kept us dry and we fell asleep again soon. /&nbsp;<span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102);">Despu&eacute;s de desayunar nos fuimos a la Playa de Focas (aunque no vimos ninguna), donde Hector se meti&oacute; a nadar en aguas de 17C. &nbsp;De ah&iacute; nos lanzamos al pueblo de Bar Harbor donde turisteamos y probamos el sandwich de langosta, muy recomendado, con cerveza de moras (Maine es exportador). Luego manejamos a la punta de la monta&ntilde;a de Cadillac, donde caminamos distrutando la vista de 360 grados y los Fuertes vientos. Tambi&eacute;n paramos en una lugar llamado Jordan Pond, precioso! De regreso en nuestro campamento, cenamos y nos acostamos temprano. A media noche nos despert&oacute; una tormenta pero despu&eacute;s de ver que la nueva tienda aguanta bien la lluvia, nos dormimos de nuevo.</span>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine080_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine081_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine082_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine083_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine084_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine085_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine086_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine087_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine088_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine089_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine090_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine091_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine092_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine093_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine094_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine095_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine096_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine097_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine098_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine099_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine100_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine101_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine102_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;</p>
<h2>July 18 - Boothbay Harbor</h2>
<p>We realized we had to leave our campsite by 10 am (and everything was wet). We dried and packed our things and drove around the park, which is gigantic. We have not used our bikes at all, and although there are many bikers here, the hills are steep and long, and we decided to pass. &nbsp;We drove Thunder Hole (but missed the high-tide thundering) and to Fabbri, a picnic area where we had lunch. We then left the park and drove towards Boothbay Harbor. We arrived to the Thisle Inn and immediately took a shower (Acadia does not have showers!) We walked a few blocks to the harbor and got tickets to see the whales tomorrow. We crossed a footbridge and had dinner at the Lobster Dock, a place by the water overlooking the harbor where you can pick your own lobster. We walked around town and had blueberry and pistachio ice cream and then went to our room. /&nbsp;<span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102);">Recogimos nuestro campamento en la ma&ntilde;ana y manejamos alrededor del parque, parando en un lugar llamado el Pozo de Truenos, una bufadora rocosa que no nos toc&oacute; ver en acci&oacute;n porque era marea baja cuando fuimos. Lonchamos en una zona de picnics llamada Fabbri, y dejamos el parque rumbo a la ciudad de Boothbay Harbor, el ultimo lugar de nuestras vacaciones. Llegamos a nuestro bed &amp; breakfast hotel y despu&eacute;s de un buen ba&ntilde;o nos fuimos al puerto, que nos queda a unas cuadras del hotel. Cruzamos un puente de pedestres y llegamos a un restaurancito con vista al puerto donde cenamos unas langostas (ya las extra&ntilde;&aacute;bamos). Luego de la cena caminamos por el pueblo y comimos unas nieves de mora y de pistache.</span>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine103_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine104_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine105_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine106_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine107_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine108_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine109_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine110_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine111_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine112_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine113_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine114_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<h2>July 19 - Whale Watching / A ver a las ballenas</h2>
<p>After breakfast at the B&amp;B we went to Pier 1 and boarded the Pink Lady II, a 92-foot long double decker that took us about 20 miles into open ocean to the whales dining areas. The whole trip takes three and one half hours, and we passed some islands, boats, birds, and lobster traps on our way. We saw a seal and finally, after a while, we started spotting the &ldquo;spouts&rdquo; that signal a whale&rsquo;s surfacing for a brief moment, when we saw their backs arching as they breathed. This would happen about 3-4 times, and the last one was a deeper arching when we saw more of the whale as it prepared to go deeper down for about 10 minutes. &nbsp;We chased the only whale we saw for a bit before heading to another spot. After a few minutes, we started spotting spouts everywhere! There were several whales all around the boat and we kept running from one end or side of the boat to the other as we enjoyed the whales. &nbsp;Sadly, we had to return and by 1 pm we were on land. We had lunch at McSeagulls where in addition to good food, they serve a great Hendrick&rsquo;s garden &ndash;a mix of a gin and tonic and a mojito. After a nap we went out again, enjoyed some shops and art galleries and then headed to the rooftop of the Boat House for dinner: scallops with maple syrup and blueberry pancakes and seafood paella. /&nbsp;<span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102);">En la ma&ntilde;ana nos fuimos al puerto a abordar el barco que nos llev&oacute; a mar abierto a ver las ballenas. El viaje de ida y vuelta lleva como 3 horas y media, y de esas casi una es solo en llegar a la zona donde las ballenas van a comer. Despu&eacute;s de mucho fijar la vista empezamos a ver la nubecita que las ballenas sueltan justo antes de salir a respirar; se les ve la espalda arqueada en lo que se hunden de nuevo, y hacen esto unas 3 o 4 veces antes de hundirse por 10 minutos, pero en la &uacute;ltima aqueada, se les ve mejor. Primero solo vimos una ballena y nos la pasamos sigui&eacute;ndola; luego el capit&aacute;n llev&oacute; el barco a otra zona y de pronto est&aacute;bamos rodeados de ballenas. Fue hermos&iacute;simo, una experiencia dif&iacute;cil de explicar. &nbsp;Luego de un rato de pasarnosla de un lado a otro del barco viendo ballenas, lleg&oacute; el momento de regresar a tierra. Ya en el puerto, lonchamos en un restaurante junto al agua; luego nos fuimos a descansar. &nbsp;En la noche caminamos por el pueblo, bobeamos en tiendas, y cenamos en la terraza del techo de un bar, con una paella de mariscos y unas escalopas con maple y hotcakes.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine115_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine116_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine117_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine118_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine119_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine120_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine121_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine122_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine123_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine124_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine125_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine126_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine127_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine128_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine129_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine130_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<h2>July 20 - Leaving Maine / Empieza el regreso</h2>
<p>Karla had a bad night and woke up with bad allergies. So, we decided to not go sea-kayaking, which was our plan for the day. Instead, we drove around Southport Island, where we saw from afar a private lighthouse and a beach, and took Route 1 on our way back. We stopped at Sarah&rsquo;s Caf&eacute; on Wiscasset for lunch and drove towards Mystic, CT, where we arrived by 6:30 pm. We stopped at the same hotel where we stayed before and went to Roosevelt 4, an Asian-fusion restaurant. /&nbsp;<span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102);">Las alergias hicieron que Karla pasara una mala noche y adem&aacute;s se sientera mal en la ma&ntilde;ana, as&iacute; que cancelamos nuestros planes de kayakear en el oce&aacute;no, y luego de dejar nuestro hotel manejamos por islas cercanas, y empzamos el regreso al pueblo de Mystic, donde paramos en nuestra venida. Una vez ah&iacute;, cenamos y nos fuimos a acostar temprano.</span></p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine131_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine132_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<h2>July 21 - Back home / En casita</h2>
<p>We left the hotel after breakfast and after a stop in Stroudsburg for lunch, we were home by 4 pm. /&nbsp;Nos pasamos el d&iacute;a manejando de regreso y a las 4 de la tarde llegamos a casa.</p>
<div>&nbsp;</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>','https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2013/maine020_thumb.jpg','2013-07-10',2013,'Maine 2013','e7f16a59-ed81-429b-86e9-aad3757d3a27');
