INSERT INTO blogs VALUES(41,'2011-toronto','Toronto','2014-11-18 02:11:26.910576','2014-12-01 04:28:30.799635','<p>We visited our friends Pam and Jim in Toronto the last week of 2011 and had a great time chatting with them, visiting museums, markets, and walking up and down the city.</p>
<h3>Around Yonge Street</h3>
<h3><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/toronto01_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/toronto02_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/toronto03_thumb.jpg" /></h3>
<p>City view from the roof top. It was cloudy and foggy most days so the visibility was poor but the view was still beautiful.</p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/toronto04_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/toronto05_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/toronto06_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/toronto07_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<p>If you look closely, you can see lake Ontario in this photo.&nbsp;</p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/toronto08_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/toronto09_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<p>Around town</p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/toronto10_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/toronto11_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<h2>At the Royal Ontario Museum (ROM)</h2>
<p>We visited the exhibition: <em>Maya, secrets of their ancient world</em> which was about the Mayas in Palenque, Mexico. Very nice exhibition but unfortunately we couldn''t take pictures of that.&nbsp;</p>
<p>But we did take pictures in the First Peoples section that shows artifacts from the native people that inhabited Canada. There were some great samples of canoes and kayaks from the 1800s as well as dresses, shoes, coats, and whatnot.&nbsp;</p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/toronto12_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/toronto13_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/toronto14_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/toronto15_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/toronto16_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/toronto17_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/toronto18_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/toronto19_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/toronto20_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/toronto21_thumb.jpg" /> <img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/toronto22_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<p>Indian cuisine for dinner</p>
