INSERT INTO blogs VALUES(50,'2011-finger-lakes','Finger Lakes','2014-11-18 02:11:27.137269','2014-12-22 15:23:22.392242','<p>The last week of June we took a one week vacation to the Finger Lakes area in up state New York. We spend the first 3 nights camping in Watkins Glen at the southern tip of the lakes (B on the maps below) and then 4 nights in a bed and breakfast on the norther tip of the lakes (C on the maps below.) / <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">A finales de Junio nos tomamos unas vacationes a los &quot;Finger Lakes&quot; en la parte norte del estado de Nueva York, los lagos son muy largos y delgados (como dedos y de ahi viene el nombre). Las primeras 3 noches acampamos en un parque estatal (la letra B en el mapa de abajo) y las otras 4 noches nos la pasamos en un bed-and-breakfast (la letra C en el &nbsp;mapa)</span></p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/trip_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;</p>
<h1>Watkins Glen State Park</h1>
<p>Our campsite. / <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">Nuestro campamento</span></p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes01_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes05_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes06_sm_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<p>The state park is a 5 minute drive to the Seneca lake. / <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">El parque esta a 5 minutos del pueblo y del lago Seneca.</span></p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes02_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes03_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes04_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;</p>
<h2>Watkins Glen Gorge</h2>
<p>Inside the state park there is a beautiful gorge. The gorge is about 1.5 miles long and 400 ft deep so makes for an great hike. / <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">Dentro del parque hay un peque&ntilde;o barranco por el que se puede caminar, el barranco es como de 2 kilometros de largo y 120 metros de profundidad.</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes07_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes08_sm_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<p>&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes09_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes10_sm_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes11_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes12_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;</p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes13_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes14_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;</p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes15_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes16_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;</p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes17_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes18_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;</p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes19_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes20_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;</p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes22_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes23_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes24_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes25_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes26_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes27_sm_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<h1>Corning, NY</h1>
<p>About 15 minutes drive from the park is the town Corning famous for its glassware. The glass museum in this town is phenomenal, we even got to create our own blown glass Christmas ornaments (the truth is that the museum employee did all the difficult work but we got to be very close to the action and actually blow the glass!) / <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">A quince minutos del campamento esta Corning, un lugar muy famoso por su vidrio y cristaleria, incluso hay un museo dedicado al vidrio que esta padrisimo y hasta nos animamos a hacer nuestro propio adorno navide&ntilde;o de vidrio soplado...bueno, la verdad es que la chava del museo hizo casi todo pero nos toco participar un poquito.</span></p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes28_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes29_sm_thumb.jpg" /><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes30_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes31_sm_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<h1>Atwater winery</h1>
<p>After our three days camping we drove to the northern part of the lakes and stop at our first winery. They didn''t have very good red wines but their Chardonnay was very good and so we bought a bottle and cheese to enjoy it on their deck. Since we had just been camping we had a few leftovers crackers, apples, and walnuts to go along with it and make if a full meal with an awesome view. / <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">Despues de la acampada nos fuimos hacia la parte norte de los lagos y paramos en una de los muchos vi&ntilde;edos y nos echamos una botellita de vino tinto con unos quesitos.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes32_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes33_sm_thumb.jpg" /><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes34_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes35_sm_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<p>After the wine we drove to our bed and breakfast, checked in and took a nap... / Despues de el vinito nos registramos en el bed and breakfast y nos echamos una siesta...</p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes47_sm_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<p>...once we woke up it was time for dinner and we were able to catch this nice sunset just outside the restaurant where we had dinner. / <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">...y desde luego una vez que nos despertamos ya teniamos hambre y nos fuimos a cenar a un pueblito por ahi mismo desde donde nos toco ver el atardecer.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes36_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes37_sm_thumb.jpg" /><b><br />
</b></p>
<h1>Taughannock Falls</h1>
<p>One of those days we drove to Ithaca, NY to just walk around. We had lunch in one of the wineries around the area (Americana, I believe) and stopped to see the Taughannock Falls. / <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">Uno de esos dias visitamos Ithaca y paramos a ver las cascadas de Taughannock.</span></p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes38_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;</p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes39_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes40_sm_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes41_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes42_sm_thumb.jpg" /><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes43_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes44_sm_thumb.jpg" /><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes45_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes46_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;</p>
<h1>Skaneateles, NY</h1>
<p>Another day we had lunch at the Thirsty Owl winery (I am starting to notice a pattern here) and drove to the town of Skaneateles (sounds like &quot;skinny-atlas&quot;) / <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">Tambien nos dimos una vuelta por otro pueblito llamado Skaneateles el cual es muy pintoresco.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes48_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes49_sm_thumb.jpg" /><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes50_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes51_sm_thumb.jpg" /><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes52_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes53_sm_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<h1>Seneca Falls, NY</h1>
<p>We also visited Seneca Falls, where the 1848 First Women''s Right Convention took place and stopped by the museum. Really interesting, sad, and uplifting stuff. / <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">Tambien visitamos otro lugar llamado Seneca Falls que es famoso por que el movimiento para el derecho de las mujeres empezo en este lugar en 1848.</span></p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes54_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;</p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes55_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes56_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;</p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes57_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;</p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes58_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;</p>
<h1>Seneca Lake</h1>
<p>After Seneca Falls we went back to Geneva and rode out bicycles around the Seneca Lake. / <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">Despues de Seneca Falls nos fuimos al lago Seneca y nos echamos un paseito en bicicleta alrededor del lago.</span></p>
<h1><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes59_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes60_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;</h1>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes61_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;</p>
<h1>Buttermilk Falls (Ithaca, NY)</h1>
<p>On our way back home we stopped at the Buttermilk Falls just outside Ithaca. / <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">De regreso a casa paramos en otro lugar que se llama &quot;Buttermilk Falls&quot; a ver otras cascadas.</span></p>
<h1><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes62_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes63_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;</h1>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes64_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes65_sm_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>','https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2011/fingerlakes19_sm_thumb.jpg','2011-07-25',2011,'Finger Lakes 2011','f6f06d24-377f-47b5-a324-e80f65ff8b98');
