INSERT INTO blogs VALUES(70,'2010-penn-roosevelt','Penn Roosevelt','2014-11-18 02:11:27.566237','2015-05-25 20:15:08.412576','<p>This Saturday while Karla was in Indiana I went camping to Penn Roosevelt State Park just outside State College. / <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">En lo que Karla estaba en Indiana me decidi irme a acampar al parque estatal Penn Roosevelt a unos cuantos minutos de State College.</span></p>
<h2>Saturday November 20th</h2>
<p>According to the Pennsylvania Department of Natural Resources&nbsp;<a target="_blank" href="http://www.dcnr.state.pa.us/stateparks/parks/pennroosevelt.aspx">Penn Roosevelt State Park</a> was created in the 1930s by members of the Civilian Conservation Corps (CCC), a group created by Roosevelt to tackle the high unemployment of the time: / <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">Segun el departamento de recursos naturales de Pennsylvania este parque fue contruido por un grupo civil formado por el presidente Roosevelt en los 30s para combatir el desempleo en la epoca de la depresion.&nbsp;</span></p>
<address style="margin-left: 40px; ">&quot;Penn-Roosevelt State Park did not exist until June 5, 1933, when members of the Civilian Conservation Corps (CCC) arrived to set up a work camp during the height of the Great Depression. The camp at Penn-Roosevelt was first known as Camp S-62, Stone Creek Kettle. The CCC of the 1930s was segregated and the camp at Stone Creek Kettle was one of only 12 Black camps in Pennsylvania. Corpsmembers lived at the camp and constructed recreational facilities, including a 195-foot log-crib dam that has since been stone-faced. They also built many of the surrounding forestry roads and trails. Two fireplaces, a unique stone bake oven and other ruins of the camp can still be found.&quot;</address>
<p>There are still a few structures from that time around including a few ovens and of course the little dam. / <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">Todavia quedan algunas de las estructuras que se irigieron en aquella epoca como los hornos que se ven en estas fotos y el peque&ntilde;o dique.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2010/pb200006_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2010/pb200008_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Although the park is surrounded by Rothrock State Forest I wasn''t able to really enjoy the trails as much as I wanted given that we are in hunting season and I didn''t want to risk becoming somebody''s dinner. Luckily the trails were clearly marked but I was a bit disappointed that I couldn''t hike as much I wanted. / <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">El parque esta en dentro de un bosque grandisimo llamado Rothrock lleno de vegetacion y caminos para pasar el rato; desafortunadamente esta es la epoca de caceria y la mayoria de los caminitos tienen un letrero que dice &quot;asegurese de vestir chaleco y gorro naranja para prevenir ser la cena de alguien mas&quot;....bueno eso de la cena lo invente yo, pero les da una idea.</span>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2010/pb200011_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2010/pb200012_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2010/pb200013_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Here are few pictures of the park. Notice how the sky changed from cloudy to clear back and forth. This made for an interesting change in temperature as well. It was very nice when the sun was shinning and there was no wind, but when the clouds rolled in and the wind kicked in the drop in temperature was noticeable. / <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">Estas son unas fotos del parque, fijate como el cielo cambia de nublado a despejado; la temperatura tambien cambiaba drasticamente cuando estaba nublado y con viento.</span></p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2010/pb200020_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2010/pb200023_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2010/pb200026_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2010/pb200030_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The campground was empty most of the day, I guess there aren''t many crazy people venturing to camp in the third week of November and hunting season in full swing, so I had the park pretty much all to my self. / <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">Siendo que es la tercera semana de Noviember y temporada de caceria no hay muchos locos que se animen a acampar y por lo tanto me toco el parque casi para mi solito.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2010/pb200032_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2010/pb200033_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>While walking around I found a bunch of logs that some people had left in another camp site, I took them to my neck of the woods (literally!) and chopped them with my mighty ax. Now the cold weather can come in :) / <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">En lo que camine por el parque me econtre le&ntilde;a que habian dejado en otros campamentos y pues me la apa&ntilde;e y la corte en pedazos mas chiquitos con my super hacha de juguete :)&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2010/pb200039_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Oh! the lovely colors of late Fall.&nbsp;</p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2010/pb200042_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2010/pb200049_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2010/pb200051_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2010/pb200053_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>My two loyal companions: Summer and Mac. / <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">Mi compa&ntilde;eros de acampada.</span></p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2010/pb200059_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>As soon as it started getting dark I got the fire going. It took my far more than one match to get it started but it was well worth it since I used it to cook dinner (steaks, beans, and tortillas) as well as coffee. Yummi! / <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">Cuando empezo a obscurecer encendi la fotaga (y vaya que le sude en esta) para calentar la cena y el cafe. No hay nada como un buen steak asado al carbon y un cafe de olla de postre.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2010/pb200067_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2010/pb200076_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>I managed to spend all Saturday without using neither the stove or the propane lantern. As a matter of fact the only electric thing around me was my camera since the phone had no reception whatsoever so I shove it away and spend the day without a clock. It was great not having even the remote idea what time it was all day long.&nbsp;Below is a picture of the full moon sometime early in the night. &nbsp;/ <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">El sabado me la lleve si usar ni la estuva ni el quinque...de hecho el unico aparato electrico en uso fue mi camara ya que como mi telefono no tenia nada de recepcion en las monta&ntilde;as lo guarde y asi que ni reloj tuve todo el dia. Afortunadamente tuve luna llena y el cielo estaba hermoso en la noche, esta foto es de la luna ya en la nochesita.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2010/pb200082_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2>Sunday November 21st&nbsp;</h2>
<p>As expected it got pretty cold overnight. According to AccuWeather the weather in Milroy (which I think is the closest weather station) was around 29 F overnight. The ground was frozen when I woke up in the morning. I love cold mornings in the woods. / <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">Como era de esperarse el clima bajo bastante en la madrugada y segun AccuWeather llegamos como a -2C y se notaba ya que todo estaba congelado</span>.&nbsp;</p>
<p>Since I couldn''t hike much in Penn Roosevelt (due to the hunting season) I decided to just drive around the Rothrock Forest through some of the roads and visit other parks around the area and see if I had better luck in other parks. The roads are gravel in some areas and paved in others and they go through several mountains. It was a great ride. Unfortunately with the overcast skies it was hard to get good pictures but here are a few of the road: <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">/ Como no podia hacer mucho por lo caminitos con eso de la epoca de caceria me decidi irme a otros parques que estan dentro del area del bosque bosque Rothrock a ver si tenia mejor suerte. Estas son algunas de la fotos que tome en lo que paseaba en el carro por ahi.</span></p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2010/pb210085_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2010/pb210095_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2010/pb210099_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2010/pb210103_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2010/pb210108_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2010/pb210117_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>After a few wrong turns I managed to make it to <a target="_blank" href="http://www.dcnr.state.pa.us/stateparks/parks/whippledam.aspx">Whipple Dam State Park</a>. The trail that goes around the lake was off the hunting area so I was able to hike that one (it''s only about 3 miles) and enjoy it with Summer and Mac. /<span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); "> Despues de un buen rato (y casi una perdida!) termine en otro parque que se llama Whipple Dam que afortunadamente tenia un camino habierto para cambiar con los perros y estaba fuera del area de caceria.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2010/pb210120_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>A love the colors of this picture. It looks like if I applied a filter to make it sepia and only leave the green stand out...but I didn''t. That''s how the picture came. This is when it''s great to have a manual mode in the camera and been able to control the settings so that the camera does not &quot;correct&quot; it for me. / <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">Estas fotos del caminito me encantan por que muestran los colores tal y como se veian dentro del bosque...todo esta de color sepia y unas cuantas plantas siguen de color verde.&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2010/pb210124_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2010/pb210128_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2010/pb210130_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The trail goes around the lake and it''s usually next to a creek. This picture reflects exactly how it felt at the bottom of the hill where the sunlight barely can make it...too bad the sound of the water in the creek didn''t come through in the picture :) / <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">El caminito var bordeando el lago y un riachuelo por un lado de un cerro. Esta foto la tome en la parte mas baja del cerro donde la luz del sol casi no entra...se veia precioso, lastima que la foto no captura el ruido del riachuelo :)</span>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2010/pb210135_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>I need to put bandannas around Summer and Mac''s necks so I don''t lose them with so many leaves! / <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">Tengo que ponerles una pa&ntilde;oletas a Summer y a Mac para que no se me pierdan con el color de las horasca!&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2010/pb210141_thumb.jpg" /></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2010/pb210143_thumb.jpg" />&nbsp;<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2010/pb210146_thumb.jpg" /></p>','https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2010/pb210135_thumb.jpg','2010-11-20',2010,'Penn Roosevelt 2010','608e09c4-f6d1-49af-9188-41d22116f847');
