<p><img alt="" border="1" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2009/NewYearA_090_thumb.JPG" />&nbsp;<img alt="" border="1" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2009/NewYearA_092_thumb.JPG" />&nbsp;</p>
<p>Awaiting the New Year, we had dinner, dessert, and played games. We then each had 12 grapes to receive the new year.</p>
<p><img alt="" border="1" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2009/NewYearA_099_thumb.JPG" />&nbsp;!<img alt="" border="1" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2009/NewYearA_101_thumb.JPG" />&nbsp;<img alt="" border="1" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2009/NewYearA_108_thumb.JPG" />&nbsp;<img alt="" border="1" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2009/P1010118_thumb.JPG" /></p>
<p>Thursday, January 1</p>
<p>Hector and Leah went snow showing to Castle Mound.</p>
<p><img alt="" border="1" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2009/PC310054_thumb.JPG" />&nbsp;<img alt="" border="1" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2009/PC310055_thumb.JPG" />&nbsp;</p>
