INSERT INTO blogs VALUES(97,'2008-paris','Paris','2014-11-18 02:11:28.169239','2015-05-25 20:47:37.026568','<p>We went back to Paris this August, and it was as amazing as the first time. Here are a few of the many pictures we took. There so many that we broke them down by day. There is a link at the end of each day to go to the next.</p>
<p><span style="color: #339966">Regresamos a Paris este agosto, y nos la pasamos tan bien como la primera vez. Aqui estan unas cuantas fotos de las muchas que tomamos. Tomamos tantas fotos que las dividimos por dia, hay una liga al final de cada pagina para ir al siguiente dia.</span></p>
<p>August 1-2/<span style="color: #339966">1 y 2 de Agosto </span></p>
<p>This was the first time we take the bus to the airport. From KC we flew to Toronto, and after the most horrible flight we have ever had (a&nbsp;poor baby near us cried literally non-stop the whole flight), we landed&nbsp;in Paris at 9:30 a.m. of Saturday, August 2.&nbsp;We took the RER and then Metro to our hotel. After a short nap, we went out to eat and walked along the Seine river, Notre Dame, and finally had a long-craved mango glace from Ile-St-Louis. Around 6 p.m. we crashed and slept 12 hours.</p>
<p><span style="color: #339966">Fue la primera vez que tomamos el camion para ir al aeropuertp. De Kansas City volamos a Toronto, Canada, y luego de 7 horas y media en un vuelo miserable (un bebe se la paso llorando sin parar), llegamos a Paris a las 9 y media de la manana del sabado.&nbsp; Tomamos el tren y metro al hotel, y luego de una siesta corta, fuimos a comer, caminar por el rio Sena, la catedral de nuestra senora, y comer las nieves de mango de la isla de San Luis que tanto anorabamos. Como a las 6 pm regresamos al hotel a dormir 12 horas.</span></p>
