INSERT INTO blogs VALUES(104,'2008-paris-2008-day-9','Paris 2008 Day 9','2014-11-18 02:11:28.301547','2014-11-18 02:11:28.301547','<p><span>Sunday, August 10/</span><span style="color: #339966"><span>Domingo 10 de agosto&nbsp;</span></span></p>
<p>It rained in the morning. Around noon&nbsp;we took the Metro to&nbsp;the neighborhood of Jardin des Plantes.&nbsp;We walked around a market, then along the street Rue Mouffetard, visited the ruins of the Lutece arena, and finally went into a&nbsp;nice restaurant, L''Assiette aux Fromages, near the Place de la Contrescarpe. We had one of the best and longest meals ever: onion soup, chicken with ratatouie, duck and potatoes, and great Bordeaux wine; later the best creme brule, cheese sampler and espressos after the meal.</p>
<p>We walked back, passing by The Pantheon and Atienne''s church. By the Seine we saw Shakespeare and Company, a bookstore with books in English (stamped &quot;Shakespeare and Co. Kilometer Zero Paris&quot;). We walked around the Seine and Ile-St-Louis, getting another ice cream, of course.</p>
<p>&nbsp;<span style="color: #339966">Llovio en la manana, asi que al medio dia nos fuimos en metro al barrio Jardin des Plantes, Caminamos por un mercado al aire libre, y por la calle Moufetard, y vimos las ruinas de la arena Lutecia. Lonchamos en un restaurante frances cerca de la plaza de la Contrescarpe. Ese fue uno de las mejores y mas largas comilonas que hemos tenido: sopa de cebolla, pollo&nbsp;con verduras a la ratatouie, pato con papas, y vino&nbsp;de Bordeaux; y de postre creme brule (como flan), quesos y expressos.&nbsp;</span><span style="color: #339966">Caminamos de regreso al rio, y llegamos a una libreria de libros en ingles: Shakespeare y Co. Despues caminamos cerca del rio y en la isla de San Louis, donde compramos otra nieve de garrafa.</span><br />
&nbsp;</p>
