INSERT INTO blogs VALUES(109,'2008-paris-2008-day-4','Paris 2008 Day 4','2014-11-18 02:11:28.397394','2014-11-18 02:11:28.397394','<p>Tuesday August 5/<span style="color: #339966">Martes 5 de agosto</span></p>
<p>We took the Metro to Abbesses and walked around Montmartre, passed the Moulin Rouge and went to the cemetery of Montmartre. We then climbed those never-ending steps up to Sacre Cour (Sacred Heart). As we walked to Place du Tertre, a lively square with restaurants, painters, mimes, and dozens of tourists, we decided to have a quiet lunch inside a restaurant, Le Sabot.&nbsp;Later, we walked in and out of shops and a gallery dedicated to Dali. When we were ready to take a break we went to the park behind Sacre Cour, where some Parisians were sunbathing (we are pretty sure they were Parisian, trust us). By the time we went back to the hotel we were ready for peace and quiet, so we had cheese, pates, fruit, bread and wine at the balcony of our hotel room.</p>
<p><span style="color: #339966">Tomamos el metro a la parada de Abeses y caminamos por el barrio de Montmartre; vimos el Molino Rojo, y nos metimos a bobear al cementerio del barrio. Despues subimos los peldanos hacia la iglesia de Sacre Cour (Sagrado Corazon). De ahi fuimos al jardin Place de Tertre, donde hay restaurantes, artistas de acuarela, mimos, y miles de turistas. Nos metimos a descansar del bullicio a un restaurante y despues turisteamos y bobeamos en las tienditas de artesanias y recuerditos, y hasta nos metimos a una galeria de cuadros y pinturas de Dali. Para descansar nos fuimos al parquecito detras de la iglesia donde parisinos y parisinas tomaban el sol. Ya tarde regresamos al hotel y cenamos en el balcon del cuarto: tablita de quesos y carnes frias con vino tinto.</span></p>
