During Memorial Day weekend (2006) we went to the Lake of the Ozarks. Here are the pictures from our trip.

<b>The Cabin</b>
We stayed in a small cabin at the <a href="http://www.rockharborresort.com/" target="other">Rock Harbor Resort</a>, pretty nice place and right by the lake. The cabins have air-conditioning which came pretty handy since the last three days the weather was in the lower 90s. The cabin came with appliances, pots, dishes and some other amenities.

<thumbnail=pictures/2006/lakeozarks_035.jpg> <thumbnail=pictures/2006/lakeozarks_022.jpg> <thumbnail=pictures/2006/lakeozarks_023.jpg> <thumbnail=pictures/2006/lakeozarks_024.jpg> <thumbnail=pictures/2006/lakeozarks_027.jpg> <thumbnail=pictures/2006/lakeozarks_029.jpg> <thumbnail=pictures/2006/lakeozarks_058.jpg> <thumbnail=pictures/2006/lakeozarks_059.jpg>

<b>Boat Ride</b>
On Saturday we rented a small boat and went around the cove where our cabin was. Our "speed boat" was really a fishing boat with a small 9.9HP engine. It was enough for the 4 of us and specially safe for a wanna-be captain that has never driven a boat on his own before.
