INSERT INTO blogs VALUES(157,'2005-smithville-lake','Smithville Lake','2014-11-18 02:11:29.439933','2015-05-25 20:57:52.806838','On Sunday, April 10th, 2005 I decided to ride the bike trails that are in <a href="http://www.northlandtrails.org/mtb.htm" target="_blank">Smithville Lake</a>. I knew little about the size of the lake and the location of the trails.

The following picture shows the route that I took.

<img src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2005/SmithvilleLake.jpg" border=1>

I started at the bottom of the lake (point 1) and tried to reach the trail by going around the lake. Next thing I knew I took a wrong turn and ended at point 2. So I had to come back until I finally reached point 3. The bike trail actually starts at point 4. Half the distance between point 4 and point 5 is a gravel road and the other half is paved road. The gravel section is pretty nice and goes along the lake shore.

By the time I got to point 5 I thought that I could keep going around the lake until the point where I started. It turned out that there is no more bike trails from that point forward so I had to go all the way down to highway MO 92 (point 6.) Highway 92 is a very busy highway, with plenty of hills, and it does not have shoulder! As a result I had to walk on the side of the road with my bike. I walked about 1/2 hr to reach point 7. From there was able to ride again until I got back to point 8.

It took me 4 hours to do this tour! I don''t even know how many miles I rode. It was fun probably the first 2 1/2 hours. The rest was just because I didn''t have any other option :) Oh well...I''ll plan better next time.

','','2005-04-10',2005,'Smithville Lake 2005','20696928-7552-475f-8498-ae53863e53c9');
INSERT INTO blogs VALUES(159,'2005-new-york','New York','2014-11-18 02:11:29.481507','2015-05-25 20:58:58.465625','On June 17th, 2005 I flew to New York for a business trip. I had some spare time on Saturday afternoon and Sunday and visited several places.

On Saturday afternoon I went to Times Square and walked around a bit. I''ve been there before and I was expecting to see a lot of people, yet, I had forgotten how it feels to be there. It is amazing to see so many people walking around. It''s a nice scene.

<div class=spanish>El 17 de junio me toco ir en un viaje de negocios a Nueva York. El sabado por la tarde y el domingo tuve un tiempecillo libre y me fue a pasear por la ciudad.

El sabado por la tarde me fui al "Times Square" a caminar un rato; a pesar de que ya habia estado ahi en una visita anterior y sabia que hay una cantidad enorme de gente, la verdad es que se me habia olvidado como se siente estar rodeado de tanta gente, es una escena muy padre.
</div>

<p align=center><img src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2005/NewYork2005_001.jpg" /></p>


From there, I took the subway and headed down to Greenwich Village, the bohemian side of New York. The weather couldn''t be any nicer. I had dinner in a little Spanish/Italian restaurant with outdoor seating.

<div class=spanish>De ahi me subi al metro y me fui a "Greenwich Village" que es la parte de bohemia de Nueva York, el clima estaba muy rico asi que me toco cenar al aire libre en un restaurant que era una mezcla entre español e italiano.</div>

<p align=center><img src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2005/NewYork2005_002.jpg" /> <img src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2005/NewYork2005_003.jpg" /></p>


Sunday I had more time to tour around so I went to Central Park and then to the <a href="http://www.moma.org" target="_blank">Museum of Modern Art.</a>  They have 6 floors of art and some beatiful pieces by Van Gogh, Pollock, Miró, Dalí, and Picasso.

<div class=spanish>El domingo me fui al "Central Park" y de ahi al Museo de Arte Contemporaneo, el cual es un museo bastante grande con 6 pisos llenos es exposiciones permanentes y piezas originales de Van Gohg, Pollock, Miró, Dalí y Picasso. </div>

<p align=center><img src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2005/vangogh_starry.jpg" /></p>

After that I walked around mid-town and took a few more pictures of the Rockefeller Plaza, the statue of Atlas, and the Chrysler Building.

<div class=spanish>De ahi me segui turisteando por el centro y tome mas fotos de la Plaza Rockefeller, la estatua del Atlas y el edificio Chryslter.</div>

<p align=center><img src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2005/NewYork2005_009a.JPG" /><br>
<img src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2005/NewYork2005_010a.JPG" />
<img src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2005/NewYork2005_011a.JPG" /></p>


I ran across a street fair on 5th Avenue and 45th Street. Really nice. Several food stands with food and crafts from all over the world.
<div class=spanish>Al final me encontre con una feria de artesinas y comida en la 5a. avenida y la calle 45.</div>

<p align=center><img src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2005/NewYork2005_004a.JPG" /></p>

','','2005-06-17',2005,'New York 2005','7dd7eac7-9834-4d42-ae25-4b50604fd4ab');
