INSERT INTO blogs VALUES(207,'2001-chicago-trip','Chicago Trip','2014-11-18 02:11:30.573164','2015-12-20 14:50:31.049221','<p><span>December 26th-30th, 2001</span></p>


<h2>December 26th ,2001</h2>
<p>Our trip started at 8 o&rsquo;clock. We rode the Amtrak. Although the trip is a little bit longer than 8 hours, it is a nice trip. All aboard!   A las 8 de la ma&ntilde;ana nos subimos al tren rumbo a Chicago. El viaje dura un poquito mas de 8 horas pero siendo nuestro primer viaje en tren ni lo sentimos. &iexcl;Vamonos!</p>

<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/chicago/chitrain.JPG" /></p>

<p>We got to Chicago just about dinner- time. We went to try the famous Chicago deep-dish pizza.   Llegamos justo a la hora de la cena y Chicago es famoso por sus pizzas. &iquest;Adivina que cenamos? :)</p>

<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/chicago/chipizza.JPG" /></p>


<h2>December 27th, 2001</h2>
<p>Our Thursday we went to the Sears Tower. They are now the second tallest building in the World. This picture shows a view of Chicago&rsquo;s downtown from their observatory.  El jueves fuimos al observatorio de la Torre Sears (el segundo edificio mas alto del mundo). Esta foto la tomamos desde ahi.</p>

<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/chicago/chiview.JPG" /></p>

<p>After the Sears Tower we spent the day walking on the &ldquo;loop&rdquo;. This area is full of beautiful buildings, with all sorts of architectural styles. The building behind me is called The Rookery.  Depues de visitar la Torre Sears nos fuimos a caminar por el centro. El centro de Chicago es muy padre y esta lleno de edificios de todos sabores y colores. El edificio que esta detras de mi se conoce como &ldquo;The Rookery&rdquo;</p>

<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/chicago/chirookery.JPG" /></p>

<p>Besides the buildings, there are a couple of famous sculptures in the loop. This one on the picture is called &ldquo;Chicago&rdquo; and it was designed by Joan Miro. You guess right, the little woman on the base of the sculpture is Karla :)  Ademas de los edificios nos encontramos un chorro de esculturas en el centro. En esta foto esta una dise&ntilde;ada por Miro. La mancha negra en la parte de abajo de la foto es Karla :)</p>

<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/chicago/chimiroscul.JPG" /></p>

<p>Here is another nice sculpture that we found on the loop. This one was designed by Picasso.   Esta es otra esculptura famosa que nos encontramos en el centro; esta fue dise&ntilde;ada por Picasso.</p>

<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/chicago/chipicasso.JPG" /></p>


<h2>December 28th ,2001</h2>

<p>On Friday we went to the Chicago Art Institute. The building itself it&rsquo;s beautiful.   El viernes nos fuimos al Instituto de Arte de Chicago.</p>

<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/chicago/chiinsart.JPG" /></p>

<p>They have a fantastic exhibit of modern art. In this picture Hector is beside a painting by Miro.  El instituto tiene una cantidad enorme de obras de arte moderno. Aqui estoy junto a una pintura de Miro.</p>

<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/chicago/chimiro.JPG" /></p>

<p>We noticed this building while we were waiting online outside the Art Institute. Isn&rsquo;t it cool?  Este edificio esta afuera del instituto. Karla me tomo la foto mientras haciamos cola para entrar.</p>
<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/chicago/chihbuild.JPG" /></p>


<h2>December 29th ,2001</h2>

<p>Saturday we spent most of the day at the Shed Aquarium.  This is the main entrance to the building.   El sabado nos la pasamos en el acuario Shed. Esta es la entrada principal al edificio.</p>

<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/chicago/chiaquarium.JPG" /></p>

<p>This is one of the many fish tanks that they have. It is amazing the number of colors that you can see on the plants and animals inside these tanks.  Esta es una de las muchas peceras dentro del acuario. Los colores tanto de las plantas como de los animales es increible.</p>

<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/chicago/chifish.JPG" /></p>

<p>From the aquarium you we were able appreciate Chicago&rsquo;s skyline better than from downtown.  Desde el acuario se pueden apreciar mejor muchos de los edificios del centro.</p>

<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/chicago/chihk.JPG" /></p>

<p>The tallest black building is the Sears Tower. This picture was taken from outside the aquarium as well.  El edificio negro es la Torre Sears.</p>

<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/chicago/chihview.JPG" /></p>

<p>The John Hancock is another skyscraper located in Chicago. The shape of this building is rather unique. This was my favorite building.   El centro John Hancock es otro de los rascacielos que se encuentra en Chicago. La forma de este edificio es muy peculiar y fue el edificio que mas me gusto.</p>

<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/chicago/chihancock.JPG" /></p>

<p>Speaking of favorites...this was Karla&rsquo;s favorite spot: The Magnificent Mile. A whole mile full of Christmas lights and shops! :)  Este fue el area que mas le gusto a Karla: La Milla Magnifica. Es una area que cubre poco mas de una milla y esta llena de tiendas, tiendas, tiendas y decoraciones navide&ntilde;as. J</p>

<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/chicago/chimiraclemile2.JPG" /></p>

<h2>December 30th ,2001</h2>

<p>On the hotel getting ready to go back home.  En el hotel listo para regresar a casita.</p>

<p><img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/chicago/chihotel.JPG" /></p>

','https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/chicago/chipizza.JPG','2001-12-26',2001,'Chicago Trip 2001','65a9ff40-2f6e-42f5-97d6-5e7a33e41f92');
INSERT INTO blogs VALUES(210,'2001-new-york','New York','2014-11-18 02:11:30.637374','2015-12-20 14:37:45.478580','<p><span>Thursday June 14th, 2001 / Jueves 14 de junio del 2001.  Karla arrived to New York City. Hector was waiting for her in the Hotel and as soon as she got there we got out! We took the subway and went to Soho, a neighborhood with a lot of Cafes, small shops and funny things to see, we had dinner there. Near there is Chinatown; we walked a few blocks in there.   <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">Karla lleg&oacute; a la ciudad de Nueva York, donde Hector la estaba esperando. Aventamos la mochila y nos fuimos de vagos. Tomamos el metro (como el del DF, pero un poco mas cochino) a Soho, un barrio pintoresco con cafes al aire libre, negocitos, gente al por mayor, ahi cenamos y caminamos al barrio chino.</span> <img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/ny_subway.jpg" /></span></p>
<hr />
<p>This church amazed us for the contrast with the other modern buildings.  Esta iglesia que nos gusto mucho por el contraste en el tipo de edificios. <img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/th_church.jpg" /></p>
<hr />
<p>Then we went to the Empire State Building, and we could see the city from floor 86th (there''s another observatory in floor 102nd but it has glass and the view isn''t that good. We could see NYC before and after it got dark, so it was beautiful!    We took some pictures from the observatory, but they didn&rsquo;t come out good. But trust us, the view is great! :)  <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">De ahi nos fuimos en metro al Empire State Building, que es donde King Kong se subio con la chavita. Era el edificio mas alto de la ciudad de Nueva York hasta hace unos a&ntilde;os, pero sigue siendo uno de los mas turisticos y bonitos. Vimos la ciudad desde el piso 86 (tiene mas de 100) hasta que anochecio.  Es muy dificil tomarle fotos sobre todo de noche. Salieron feas la mayoria de nuestras fotos desde el mirador. Pero creannos,la vista de la ciudad desde alla&nbsp;</span><span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">arriba es hermosa.</span></p>
<p><img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/th_empirestate_tall.jpg" /> <img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/th_empirestate.jpg" /></p>
<hr />
<p>From there we took the subway to Times Square, where we could see the night signs and lots of people, walking, taking pictures &ndash;many tourists-, playing musical instruments, eating, shopping, etc.  <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">Otra vez en metro nos fuimos a Times Square, que es otro de los lugares mas turisticos de la ciudad (claro, fuimos a puros lugares turisticos, como buenos turistas jajajaja, que babas no?) ahi estan muchos de los teatros de Broadway, letreros luminosos de varios pisos, gente tocando, bailando, vendiendo, y decenas de turistas.</span></p>
<p><img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/th_timessquare1.jpg" /> <img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/th_timessquare2.jpg" /> <img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/th_timessquare3.jpg" /> <img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/th_kiss.jpg" /></p>
<hr />
<p>Yet another cool building in downtown Manhattan.  Otro edificio padre en el centro de Manhattan <img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/th_mirror.jpg" /></p>
<hr />
<p>Karla walking in the Fifth Avenue.  Karla paseando por la Quinta avenida.  <img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/th_5thavenue.jpg" /></p>
<p>Then we took a taxi to the Rockefeller Center (where the NBC and ABC stations are). We took a ride in a horse-pulled car, which Karla though was dangerous for NYC. We finished that night in a cafe, after walking for hours. Karla got blisters from this very first day from all the walking. Hector didn&rsquo;t; he&rsquo;s not human.  The long picture below shows Times Square really good.    <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">Esta vez en taxi (que es como en Colima, los tomas en cada esquina, no como en Kansas, que nomas por telefono) nos fuimos al Rockefeller Center que es donde estan las televisoras nacionales de dos canales enormes (como Televisa), tomamos un paseo en calandria, &iexcl;imaginense en Nueva York! Karla sentia que un pinche taxi se nos iba a echar encima y voltear la carreta, en serio, son re cafres. &iexcl;Ni disfruto Karla el mendigo paseo caro!   Terminamos la noche en un cafe cerca del hotel. Por cierto, el hotel estaba a una cuadra de Broadway, tres de la Quinta avenida y dos de Central Park. Todo nos quedaba cerca.</span></p>
<p><img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/th_timessquare_wide.jpg" /></p>

<h2>Friday June 15th, 2001</h2>
<p>Friday June 15th, 2001 / Viernes 15 de junio del 2001.  Karla woke up with blisters, so she put on some Band-Aids and tennis shoes. We went (in the subway again) to the station where we could get the ferry to the Statue of the Liberty and Ellis Island.   The size of the statue can be seen if you notice the little people in the picture of the foot.  The statue is not filled, it&rsquo;s made of copper with a two-penny thickness and people can go to the crown to see NYC. &nbsp;<span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">Karla amanecio con ampollas; se puso curitas y tenis y los dos salimos a la calle desde temprano. Nos fuimos en metro a la estacion donde tomamos la lancha para la Estatua de la Libertad y la isla Ellis. La estatua es imponente, bella y parece que a los Europeos les causa mucha mas emocion que a los Mexicanitos :)  Para que se den cuenta del tama&ntilde;o de la estatua, vean la patita de la se&ntilde;ora y la gente debajo (casi no se ven). No esta rellena, sino que es una cubierta de metal del grosor de 2 monedas de diez centavos. La gente sube al mirador que esta en la frente de la estatua.</span></p>
<p><img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/fr_statue1.jpg" /> <img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/fr_statue2.jpg" /></p>
<p><img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/fr_statue_back.jpg" /> <img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/fr_statue_foot.jpg" /></p>
<p><img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/fr_laughing.jpg" /></p>
<hr />
<p>This was funny :)  Chequense esto :) <img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/fr_lady.jpg" /></p>
<hr />
<p>The city of New York behind us from the island. It was a foggy day.  Nueva York se ve desde la isla. Como veran estaba aneblinado.  <img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/fr_manhattan.jpg" /></p>
<hr />
<p>Ellis Island was the entering port where millions of immigrants arrived to the States. We liked this place a lot. It''s a museum with migration info, and it''s a cool place. &nbsp;<span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">La isla Ellis es donde estaban las oficinas de migracion y recibian a los miles de inmigrantes de Europa por decadas. Ahora es un museo con la infomacion de toda la gente que vino a poblar Estados Unidos</span>.</p>
<p><img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/fr_ellis1.jpg" /> <img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/fr_ellis2.jpg" /> <img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/fr_ellis3.jpg" /> <img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/fr_ferry.jpg" /></p>
<hr />
<p>After that we walked to Wall Street (just a few blocks from the ferry station) and we saw the Stock Exchange Buildings. All the buildings are so tall that we barely could see the sunlight in there. And it was a busy day there.    <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">Despues de ahi caminamos a Wall Street que quedaba a unas cuantas cuadras.  Los edificios son enormes y pegaditos, asi que no llega la luz del sol tan facil. Ahi estaban los trajeados jugandose millones de dolarucos.</span></p>
<p><img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/fr_wallst.jpg" /> <img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/fr_wallst_buildings.jpg" /> <img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/fr_wallst_church.jpg" /> <img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/fr_wallst_federalhall.jpg" /> <img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/fr_wallst_bull.jpg" /></p>
<p>Then we walked to the World Trade Center, which is now the tallest building in NYC (although New Yorkers love the Empire State the most... I wonder if it''s because of king Kong).  The World Trade Center is a four-buildings place where two of them are the skyscrapers. In the bottom there''s a mall.  <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">De ahi caminamos al World Trade Center, un conjunto de cuatro edificios, dos de ellos los rascacielos mas altos de NY. Abajo es un centro comercial.</span></p>
<p><img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/fr_wtc.jpg" /> <img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/fr_wtc2.jpg" /></p>
<hr />
<p>From there we went to see the Brooklyn Bridge, so we could also stop and see the City Hall. We walked to South St Seaport where there''s an open area with restaurants and shops. We had a nice dinner there. We walked around the area, which seemed like a downtown-type, with lots of small stores, cafes, bookstores, etc.  <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">De ahi al puente Brooklyn, un puente hermoso y famosisimo arquitectonicamente. Paseamos por la bahia y cenamos ahi, en unas sombrillitas al aire libre. Paseamos por ese lado de la ciudad y de regreso antes de ir al hotel estuvimos en una esquina de Central Park.</span></p>
<p><img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/fr_brooklyn1.jpg" />  <img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/fr_brooklyn2.jpg" /> <img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/fr_brooklyn_column.jpg" /> <img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/fr_brooklyn_wtc.jpg" /> <img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/fr_brooklyn_manhattan.jpg" /></p>
<hr />
<p>Hector in Central Park. Isn&rsquo;t he handsome?  Hector en Central Park. &iquest;A poco no esta guapisimo? <img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/fr_centralpark.jpg" /></p>

<h2>Saturday June 16th, 2001</h2>
<p>Saturday June 16th, 2001 / Sabado 16 de junio del 2001.  On Saturday we went to the Metropolitan Museum of Art (MET). It''s huge and beautiful! It hosted about 20 or 30 exhibitions and we were able to see just one: The Egyptians, and part of the Greeks. We were there for hours.  <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">El sabado ya estabamos muertos, ampollados, acalambrados, pero con muchas ganas de seguir viendo la ciudad. Nos fuimos al Museo Metropolitano de Arte. &iexcl;Hermoso! &iexcl;Enorme! &iexcl;Divino! &iexcl;Imponente! Albergaba cerca de 30 exposiciones y nomas tuvimos tiempo de ver una entera (Egipto) y dos de pasadita (fotos de Grecia), sin leer los letreritos. Imaginense lo enorme. Duramos ahi como 4 o 6 horas.</span></p>
<p><img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/sa_met1.jpg" /> <img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/sa_met2.jpg" /> <img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/sa_met3.jpg" /> <img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/sa_met4.jpg" /> <img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/sa_met5.jpg" /></p>
<hr />
<p>After the MET, we took a taxi to FAO Schwartz and walk around looking for a place to eat. It rained for a few minutes.   <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">De ahi tomamos un taxi a FAO Swarchtz que es una tienda de juguetes. Ahi se filmo parte de la pelicula Mi Pobre Angelito. Caminamos hasta hallar donde comer y caminamos por la Quinta avenida</span>.</p>
<p><img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/sa_fao.jpg" /></p>
<hr />
<p>Just walking around...  Nomas paseando... <img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/sa_church.jpg" /> <img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/sa_ibm.jpg" /></p>
<hr />
<p>Then we walked to Times Square, which is impressive, especially at night, with all the screens, noises, music, people, businesses, etc.   Hector took Karla to a nice restaurant-bar to have a drink and rest. Karla&rsquo;s feet were hurting so bad by then and she had Band-Aids everywhere!   <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">De ahi a Times Square de nuevo (nos gusto mucho). Nos fuimos en taxi a un restaurante a tomar unas cervecitas y descansar antes de irnos a dormir.</span></p>
<p><img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/sa_timessquare.jpg" /></p>

<h2>Sunday June 17th, 2001</h2>
<p><span>Sunday June 17th, 2001 / Domingo 17 de junio del 2001.  On Sunday we went to the Museum of Natural History and even though we tried to find Dr. Ross (from the TV show Friends) we didn''t see him anywhere. It''s a great museum too. We saw the Dinosaurs, the Human Evolution, The Genome and the Big Bang exhibitions.  <span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">El domingo nos costo un chorro levantarnos. Nos fuimos al Museo de Historia Natural, tambien enfrente de Central Park, pero como a 30 cuadras del hotel (Central Park es enorme). El museo estuvo precioso. Vimos los dinosaurios, el DNA, la evolucion humana. Increible, moderno, espacioso. Y nosotros muertos de cansancio.</span></span></p>
<p><span>   <img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/su_nhma6.jpg" /> <img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/su_nhma5.jpg" /> </span></p>
<p><span><img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/su_nhma1.jpg" /> <img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/su_nhma2.jpg" /> </span></p>
<p><span><img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/su_nhma4.jpg" /> <img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/su_nhma3.jpg" /> </span></p>
<p><span> <img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/su_nhma_horns.jpg" /> <img border="1" alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/su_nhma7.jpg" /></span></p>
<p>From there we walked a little in Central Park, which is a huge park, I think it''s like 1/4 of the Manhattan''s size. Following that, we went to the Lincoln Center where there was kind of a fair event on the open. We walked around the booths and had dinner there.&nbsp;<span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">De ahi nos fuimos a caminar por Central Park, como una hora, nomas alcanzamos a ver un pedacito. Es tan grande que hay calles con semaforos, restaurantes, lagos, teatros, etc, adentro. De ahi nos fuimos al Lincoln Center, que es como un centro comercial y bobeamos un rato, ahi comimos unos sandwiches.</span></p>
<p>We went to the hotel to rest and at night we went to a nice Italian restaurant to have a few drinks.   Finally, on Monday, we had breakfast in the first Blimpie of NYC and walked to Times Square.  We went to the airport and arrived to KC around 7pm (after another delay). The city reminded me a lot to Mexico City: gray, busy, crowded, and big. Karla liked Mexico City''s subway better, it was cleaner. We didn''t see crazy people or dangerous places, situations or persons. It was not as crowded as she thought it was going to be and safer too.&nbsp;<span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">Fuimos a descansar al hotel y en la noche nos fuimos a un restaurante-bar a tomar unas cervezas. El lunes fuimos a desayunar y caminamos por Times Square antes de tomar un taxi al aeropuerto. Estabamos muertos. El avion se retraso un poco y finalmente llegamos a casa cuando estaba anocheciendo. Esa semana nos costo un chorro levantarnos para ir a trabajar, pero la verdad estamos super contentos de haber ido y aprovechado los pocos dias que tuvimos.</span></p>
<p>The hotel was a block from Broadway (three from Fifth Ave.) and two from Central Park, so we were in a great location. I really liked my trip.&nbsp;<span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 102); ">En general, Nueva York nos gusto mucho. Se parece al DF: gris, grande, lleno de gente. Vimos muchos turistas. Tal vez eso ayudo a que no vieramos violencia o inseguridad. Es una ciudad llena de vida, colores, actividades y gente de todos los lados del mundo.</span></p>


','https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2001/newyork/fr_statue2.jpg','2001-06-14',2001,'New York 2001','efedc67e-0c30-4476-9dfb-718515d5a83d');
INSERT INTO blogs VALUES(212,'2000-when-we-were-babies','When We Were Babies','2014-11-18 02:11:30.700047','2015-05-25 19:42:56.530533','<p>On our last trip to Colima, Karla brought with her her album when she was a little girl. As you can tell from the picture, Karla has always loved desserts, big desserts. Isn''t she cute? </p>
<p align=center><img src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/misc/karla.jpg" /></p>

<p>Here is Hector as a baby. Notice also how Hector loved drinking since his early years :)</p>
