INSERT INTO blogs VALUES(258,'2016-morocco','Morocco','2017-01-14 16:52:11.423951','2017-01-14 20:51:20.457871','<p>December 26, 2016 to January 5, 2017</p>

<h2>Monday, December 26, 2016</h2>

<p>Our flight from JFK was pleasant, with a woman pilot at the helm. We landed in Casablanca, Morocco at 8:30am of Tuesday. / <span class="spanish">El lunes fue día de viaje y llegamos a Casablanca, Marruecos a las 8:30 de la mañana del martes.</span></p>

<h2>Tuesday, December 27</h2>

<p>After passing through immigration and changing some US dollars for Dirhams, we took a taxi to our hotel (one-hour drive). Once at the Kenzi Basma Hotel, we were told to wait one hour for our room, so we went to the Café at the corner for a coffee. As soon as we got into our room, we took a nap. We woke up dizzy and hungry and went for rotisserie chicken to Snacks Saladin, around the corner, a restaurant we went back to more than once. We shared a half-chicken with lentil soup, innards soup, bread, and frites. After eating we walked towards the Port, and reached the train terminal, Casa Port. We were also learning how to cross the streets in this traffic-heavy and chaotic (to us) city. We entered a little bit of the Medina (enclosed old downtown with lots of souks or markets, with an impressive arched entrance). Back to our hotel area, we saw the Post Office, whose blue façade displays zellij tilework. We then sat at a Café at the Place Nations Unies to admire the art deco buildings. / <span class="spanish">Una vez que pasamos por migración y sacamos moneda nacional, tomamos un taxi al hotel, a una hora del aeropuerto. Ya en el hotel, tomamos un café en la esquina en lo que preparaban en cuarto. Luego de una siesta, salimos a buscar comida, y la hallamos a la vuelta del hotel: Pollo rostizado con sopa de lentejas, sopa de menudencias, pan, y papas a la francesa. De ahí caminamos un poco, hacia la estación de trenes. Vimos la entrada a la Medina, la parte vieja de la ciudad, con su entrada con arco de fortaleza. De regreso al área del hotel caminamos por la zona y vimos la fachada de azulejo azul de la casa de correos. Para descansar, nos sentamos en un café de la Plaza de las Naciones Unidas a ver gente.</span></p>

<p>
