</p>

<h2>Tuesday, January 3</h2>

<p>Rest day, we are dead tired. We ate at Saladin, and then sat at the plaza. We then had tea across the hotel and after getting pastries at Maryliz for the morning, we went back to rest in our room, watching TV. / <span class="spanish">Día de descanso, estamos molidos. Comimos en el lugar de pollos de a la vuelta de la esquina y nos sentamos a ver gente en la plaza. Fuimos al café de enfrente del hotel por te de menta, compramos pan dulce en la panadería de a un lado y regresamos al cuarto, a ver tele.</span></p>

<p>
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2016/morocco00120_thumb.jpg" />
</p>

<h2>Wednesday, January 4</h2>

<p>Last full day in the city. We took a petit taxi to the Habous, went back to Grillade Ait Baamran, and this time sat near the grill. Hector pointed to the meats he wanted and after a while, a server came with a package of raw meats to show us. We said yes. He drew with his finger on the table 5-0. Only then we realized we had to pay for the meat (which they got from the butcher across the street). And then waited for our food. It was delicious: kefta and salchichas.
After out meal we wandered in and out of shops, looking for a tray until we found it. I also found a bag for Karla. We took a taxi back to the hotel. That night we ate in bed again, and made our bags. We are tired but happy. / <span class="spanish">Último día entero en la ciudad. Regresamos al barrio Habous y regresamos al restaurant Grillade Ait Baamran, pero esta vez nos sentamos junto al asador y Héctor se paró a apuntar qué carnes queríamos. Luego de un rato, un mesero regreso con un bulto de carne cruda envuelta en plástico y asentimos que sí, eso era lo que queríamos. El mesero dibujó 5-0 en la mesa con el dedo, indicando que debíamos pagar por la carne (de la carnicería de enfrente). Luego de esperar a que cocinaran las carnes, finalmente comimos kefta (borrego molido y asado), salchichas asadas y acompañamientos. Después de comer bobeamos por los puestos, buscando una charola de metal y nos hallamos una bolsa para Karla. Esa noche empacamos y cenamos en cama de nuevo. Super cansados y felices.</span></p>

<p>
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2016/morocco00121_thumb.jpg" />
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2016/morocco00122_thumb.jpg" />
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2016/morocco00123_thumb.jpg" />
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2016/morocco00124_thumb.jpg" />
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2016/morocco00125_thumb.jpg" />
<img alt="" src="https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2016/morocco00126_thumb.jpg" />
</p>

<h2>Thursday, January 5</h2>

<p>We checked out from our hotel, got a grand taxi and arrived early to the Mohammed V airport. After figuring out the lines to the checking points at our gate, and then to the shuttle, we finally boarded. Once in the plane, we traded a place with a passenger so Hector and I could sit together. We had an uneventful flight. Landed on time at 6, passed through immigration, got in our car, and arrived home by 10 pm. The next day we woke up and it was snowing. / <span class="spanish">Dejamos el hotel en taxi al aeropuerto. Las colas para todo estuvieron larguísimas pero sin problemas. Ya en el avión, convencimos a alguien que cambiara asientos para que nos sentáramos juntos. El vuelo estuvo sin contratiempos. Aterrizamos a las 6 de la tarde en Nueva York y luego de pasar por migración y hallar el carro, regresamos hacia casa, a donde llegamos a las 10 de la noche. A la mañana siguiente, cuando nos despertamos, estaba nevando.</span></p>
','https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/hectorykarla/2016/morocco00013_thumb.jpg','2016-12-27',2016,NULL,NULL);
